Activity by Board of Treatment, Age and Sex

library(tidyverse)
library(infer)
age_sex <- read_csv("../clean_data/age_and_sex.csv")

Age

# Number of stays by age
by_age <- age_sex %>% 
  select(year_quarter, age, stays) %>% 
  group_by(year_quarter, age) %>% 
  summarise(stays_count =  sum(stays)) %>% 
  ungroup()
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'year_quarter'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.
by_age %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = year_quarter, y = stays_count, colour = age, group = age)) +
  geom_line() +
  geom_point() +
  scale_y_continuous(labels = scales::comma) +
  scale_colour_discrete(name = "Age") +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1)) +
  labs(
    title = "Stays by age",
    x = "\nQuarter ending",
    y = "Stays count\n")

# Mean length of stay by age
by_age <- age_sex %>% 
  select(year_quarter, age, average_length_of_stay) %>% 
  group_by(year_quarter, age) %>% 
  summarise(mean_stay =  mean(average_length_of_stay, na.rm = TRUE)) %>% 
  ungroup()
## `summarise()` has grouped output by 'year_quarter'. You can override using the
## `.groups` argument.
by_age %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = year_quarter, y = mean_stay, colour = age, group = age)) +
  geom_line() +
  geom_point() +
  scale_colour_discrete(name = "Age") +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 45, hjust = 1)) +
  labs(
    title = "Length of Stay by Age",
    x = "\nQuarter ending",
    y = "Mean Length of Stay in Days\n")
